---
import Default from '../layouts/Default.astro';
---
<Default title="Now · Harshith Kantamneni" description="What I'm working on this week." current="now">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-1" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-2" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="index-number">Now / week of May 6, 2026</span>
      <h1 style="max-width: 18ch;">What I am working on this week.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        A weekly snapshot of the labs: what's running, what's shipping, what's blocked,
        and what's on my mind. Updated weekly. Not a complete log, just a single-page
        picture of the current state.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container-narrow">

      <h2>This week</h2>
      <p>
        HIVE is at Cycle 114. The architecture port from the sister Autonomous
        Research Lab landed phase one (handoff schemas, telemetry foundation,
        brief assembler, archival sweep). Build cadence is strong: a twelve-cycle
        chain of byte-identical cross-platform builds, with the deferred-impl
        ledger holding clean for thirteen consecutive cycles.
      </p>
      <p>
        Building this site in parallel. First report drafted, three notes
        published, voice calibration ongoing.
      </p>

      <h2>What is blocking</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
        <li>Three proposals pending PI ratification (cargo-deny advisories, heuristic-candidate falsifier separation, cross-family adversary spec). Some have aged into HIGH territory.</li>
        <li>Cross-family verifier mechanism. Testing Qwen2.5-Coder-14B locally before any ratification.</li>
        <li>iOS Simulator runtime install. Long-deferred environment dependency.</li>
        <li>Patent counsel scoping consultation. Deferred until the first publishable mechanism.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I am reading</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
        <li>MAST taxonomy (arxiv 2503.13657). Multi-agent LLM failure modes.</li>
        <li>Preference Leakage paper (ICLR 2026). Same-family LLM judge bias.</li>
        <li>LightMem (ICLR 2026). Sleep-time memory consolidation.</li>
        <li>Behavioral Calibration via RL (arxiv 2512.19920).</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-7); color: var(--text-tertiary); font-size: var(--fs-small);">
        Inspired by Derek Sivers' /now movement. Updated weekly.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

</Default>
